#### Level 1: Fast Movement
Your speed increases by 10 feet while you aren't wearing Heavy armor.

#### Level 1: Blood Casting
_**Spell Slots**_. The Bloodrager Features table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your level 1+ spells. You regain all expended slots when you finish a Long Rest.

_**Prepared Spells of Level 1+**_. You prepare the list of level 1+ spells that are available for you to cast with this feature. To start, choose two level 1 Sorcerer spells. 

The number of spells on your list increases as you gain Bloodrager levels, as shown in the Prepared Spells column of the Bloodrager Features table. Whenever that number increases, choose additional Bloodrager spells until the number of spells on your list matches the number in the Bloodrager Features table. The chosen spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. 

If another Bloodrager feature gives you spells that you always have prepared, those spells don't count against the number of spells you can prepare with this feature.

_**Changing Your Prepared Spells**_. Whenever you gain a Bloodrager level, you can replace one spell on your list with another Sorcerer spell for which you have spell slots.

_**Spellcasting Ability**_. Charisma is your spellcasting ability for your Bloodrager spells.

_**Spellcasting Focus**_. You can use an [Arcane Focus](https://5e.tools/items.html#arcane%20focus_xphb) as a [Spellcasting Focus](https://5e.tools/variantrules.html#spellcasting%20focus_xphb) for your Bloodrager spells.

#### Level 2: Bloodrage
Starting at 1st level, you can tap into your primal power to enter a bloodrage.

On your turn, you can enter a bloodrage as a bonus action. While bloodraging, you gain the following benefits:

- You gain a +4 bonus to Strength and Constitution.
- You gain a +2 bonus to Wisdom saving throws.
- You take a -2 penalty to Armor Class.
- You gain 2 additional temporary hit points per level. These temporary hit points vanish when your bloodrage ends.

While bloodraging, you can only use or concentrate on Sorcerer spells. Spells from other classes cannot be cast during this state. Additionally, you can’t use Charisma-, Dexterity-, or Intelligence-based skills, except for Acrobatics, Fly, Intimidate, and Ride.

Your bloodrage lasts for 1 minute. It ends early if you are knocked unconscious. You can also end your bloodrage on your turn as a bonus action.

When your bloodrage ends, you become fatigued for a number of rounds equal to twice the number of rounds you spent bloodraging. While fatigued, you can’t enter another bloodrage.

You can bloodrage a number of times equal to your Constitution modifier (minimum of 1). You regain all expended uses of your bloodrage when you finish a long rest.

#### Level 3: Bloodrager Subclass
You gain a Bloodrager subclass of your choice. A subclass is a specialization that grants you features at certain Bloodrager levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of your subclass's features that are of your Bloodrager level or lower.

