#### Level 4: Ability Score Improvement
You gain the [Ability Score Improvement](https://5e.tools/feats.html#ability%20score%20improvement_xphb) feat or another [feat](https://5e.tools/feats.html) of your choice for which you qualify. 

#### Level 5: Extra Attack
You can attack twice instead of once whenever you take the [Attack](https://5e.tools/actions.html#attack_xphb) action on your turn.

#### Level 6: Blood Sanctuary
Due to the power of his blood, a bloodrager can stand confidently amid the effects of spells cast by himself or his allies. 
- He gains a +2 bonus on saving throws against spells that he or an ally casts.
- Additionally, when you succeed on a saving throw against a spell you cast, you can choose to take no damage or ignore the spell’s effects entirely, as if you had succeeded on a saving throw against a spell with no effect on a success

#### Level 7: Subclass Feature
You gain a feature from your Bloodrager subclass.

#### Level 8: Ability Score Improvement
You gain the [Ability Score Improvement](https://5e.tools/feats.html#ability%20score%20improvement_xphb) feat or another [feat](https://5e.tools/feats.html) of your choice for which you qualify. 

#### Level 10: Subclass Feature
You gain a feature from your Bloodrager subclass.

#### Level 11: Greater Bloodrage
When you enter a bloodrage, the bonuses granted by your rage increase. You gain the following benefits while bloodraging:
- Your Strength and Constitution bonuses increase to +6.
- Your bonus on Wisdom saving throws increases to +3.

Additionally, when you enter a bloodrage, you can cast one of your known spells of 2nd level or lower on yourself as part of the same action. The spell must target only you or have a range of touch. If the spell’s duration is longer than 1 round, it lasts until your bloodrage ends.

Casting the spell in this way consumes a spell slot as normal, and you must have the appropriate spell slot available to use this feature.

#### Level 12: Ability Score Improvement
You gain the [Ability Score Improvement](https://5e.tools/feats.html#ability%20score%20improvement_xphb) feat or another [feat](https://5e.tools/feats.html) of your choice for which you qualify. 

#### Level 13: Indomitable Will
Bloodrager gains a +4 bonus on Intelligence, Wisdom and Charisma saves to resist enchantment spells while bloodraging. This bonus stacks with all other modifiers, including the  bonus he also receives during his bloodrage.

#### Level 15: Subclass Feature
You gain a feature from your Bloodrager subclass.

#### Level 16: Ability Score Improvement
You gain the [Ability Score Improvement](https://5e.tools/feats.html#ability%20score%20improvement_xphb) feat or another [feat](https://5e.tools/feats.html) of your choice for which you qualify.

#### Level 17: Tireless Bloodrage
The bloodrager no longer becomes  fatigued at the end of his bloodrage.

#### Level 19: Epic Boon
You gain an [Epic Boon feat](https://5e.tools/feats.html#blankhash,flstcategory:eb=1) or another [feat](https://5e.tools/feats.html) of your choice for which you qualify. 

#### Level 20: Mighty Bloodrage
At 20th level, your bloodrage reaches its peak power, granting you unmatched ferocity. While bloodraging, you gain the following benefits:

- Your Strength and Constitution bonuses increase to +8.
- Your bonus on Wisdom saving throws increases to +4.

Additionally, when you enter a bloodrage, you can cast any spell you know on yourself, regardless of its level, as part of the same action. The spell must target only you or have a range of touch. If the spell’s duration is longer than 1 round, it lasts until your bloodrage ends.

 
